    public static interface ImperativeCommand.Environment

        void logMessage(@NotNull

      • generateValue

        <T> T generateValue(@NotNull
                    Generator<T> generator,
                    @Nullable
                    String logMessage)
        Generate a pseudo-random value using the given generator. Optionally log a message, so that when a test fails, you'd know the value was generated. The message is a Java format string, so you can use it to include the generated value, e.g. String s = generateValue(stringsOf(asciiLetters(), "Generated %s").

        If you don't want to generate message, or would like to show the generated value in a custom way, pass null. You can use logMessage(java.lang.String) later to still leave a trace of this value generation in the log.

        Consider making generators non-shrinkable (by invoking Generator.noShrink()) where possible because it can speed up overall failing scenario shrinking significantly.
